Findings.Title: Lambda.2 Lambda functions should use supported runtimes
Findings.Description: This AWS control checks that the lambda function settings for runtimes, match the expected values set for the supported runtimes for each language. The supported runtimes this control checks for are: nodejs14.x, nodejs12.x, python3.8, python3.7, python3.6, java11, java8, go1.x, dotnet6, dotnetcore3.1, ruby2.7.

Recommendation.Text: For directions on how to fix this issue, consult the AWS Security Hub Foundational Security Best Practices documentation.

Findings.Title: Lambda.1 Lambda function policies should prohibit public access
Findings.Description: This control checks whether the AWS Lambda function policy attached to the Lambda resource prohibits public access. If the Lambda function policy allows public access, the control fails.

Recommendation.Text: For directions on how to fix this issue, consult the AWS Security Hub Foundational Security Best Practices documentation.
